sekai-kb template marker.

While this file exists, the genericity + English-only gates run in TEMPLATE MODE:
they scan the WHOLE repository, not just the code trees (src/, scripts/, tests/,
workers/). The sekai-kb template ships zero real-place strings, so the whole tree —
including knowledge/, place.config.ts, and docs/ — must stay free of denylisted
place names and CJK codepoints.

`npm run init` (the adoption wizard) deletes this file when you adopt the template.
The gates then revert to INSTANCE MODE (code trees only), where knowledge/ and
place.config.ts legitimately carry your place's identity.

See scripts/ci/check-genericity.sh and scripts/ci/check-english-only.mjs.
